## Argument Reference

The following arguments are supported:

* `name` - (string, Required) The name for the snapshot.

* `machine_id` - (string, Required) The ID of the machine of which to take a snapshot.

## Attribute Reference

The following attributes are exported:

* `id` - (string) - The identifier representing the snapshot in Triton.
* `state` - (string) - The current state of the snapshot.

## Import

`triton_snapshot` resources can be imported using the instance UUID and snapshot UUID separated by a dot (`.`), for example:

```
$ terraform import triton_snapshot.example e0751502-45dd-4e47-8a6c-2c1f67aa2d58.c8ad8001-b1c8-4dcf-87b9-cd57fbf3b2f2
```
